{"TopicId":135386,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Nuclear Powered jet engines","CreatedByName":"He_162","CreatedById":152811,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T18:42:24Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"He_162","CreatedById":152811,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T18:42:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EI would like to know if anyone would like to make a mod adding in a nuclear powered jet engine, it looks like this:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Kjc5X.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Kjc5X.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EI will explain how this works here in a few sections:\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#0000FF;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EReactor:\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EThe reactor will come in three sizes, the small, medium, and large.\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EThose reactors are sized 0.625m, 1.250m and 2m.\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#0000FF;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003ECooling System:\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EThey all produce a large amount of heat, so a cooling unit of the same sizes should be able to be attached to the front, that is the circular tune on the front of the reactor in the picture\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#0000FF;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EEngines:\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EThe jet engines in-game are the ones that will be used, however, they need to be attached to a special fuselage structure that comes in the sizes 0.625, 1.250 and 2m, that structure will need to be connected to the reactor\u0027s cooling system via a special vent that works just like a external fuel line, when the jet engines are attached to those fuselage pieces, they then work using the heat of the reactor, and not liquid fuel.\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#0000FF;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EFuel:\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EYou can bring onboard uranium and control rods, the control rods break down over time, so you need to bring a little extra, with the uranium rods, and the throttle opens or closes the control rods. The lower the throttle, the higher the control rods go in the reactor, and the less heat they produce, reducing the thrust, when the throttle hits zero, the reactor shuts off, and it cannot be started again until it cools down all the way. When it is past 75% throttle, it will very slowly overheat, and melt down, or simply cause the reactor to stop working, and the nuclear reaction will cause it to melt, and explode.\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#0000FF;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EProtection:\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003Ethe reactor and cooling system need to weigh at least 10 tons each, because they are surrounded by solid lead to prevent radiation from escaping.\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EI hope this isn\u0027t too complicated of a request, but it would be really cool to see, and it isn\u0027t made up either, the idea came from the X-6 research craft, which would use a nuclear reactor to fly.\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EIt was only cancelled due to the probability of the aircraft being shot down, and causing nuclear waste to fall over cities, killing people, but it works in theory, math, and practice if they ever decided to do it.\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003EHEY, IF IT WORKS IN REAL LIFE, WHY NOT IN KSP?\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EAnd yes, I know there are mods with nuclear turbojets, but they are never realistic about the throttling with control rods, or with the jet propulsion part of it, the reactor simply superheats the air in place of fuel, making it run for years on end without having to do anything but have a couple storage area\u0027s with 100 control rods or so (1 control rod every week for a reactor of the biggest size 2m)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EPictures:\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Northrop_Nuclear_concept.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.airfields-freeman.com/ID/Northrop_Nuclear_concept.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ANP53%20aircraft%20mounting.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022706\u0022 src=\u0022https://photos1.blogger.com/blogger/4956/2802/1600/ANP53%20aircraft%20mounting.gif\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022tu-119-nuclear-aircraft.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.projectoceanvision.com/vox/images/chapter06/tu-119-nuclear-aircraft.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022anp-ic-2.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.aviation-history.com/articles/anp-ic-2.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;line-height:35.2px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"He_162","CreatedById":152811,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T19:11:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will make some simple drawings to make out the various parts and what they should look like in-game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ENUCLEAR ENGINES INCORPORATED, is the name, and the short version will be called \u0022NEIN\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-30T19:12:19Z\u0022 title=\u002203/30/2016 07:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by He_162\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"He_162","CreatedById":152811,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T19:46:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere are the drawings for what the parts should look like (I will take suggestions for better texture idea\u0027s, or something)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe class=\u0022imgur-album\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022550\u0022 src=\u0022//imgur.com/a/6g3qW/embed?background=ffffff\u0026amp;text=1a1a1a\u0026amp;link=4e76c9\u0022 width=\u0022100%\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gojira1000","CreatedById":152681,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T19:47:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/94519-105-atomic-age-nuclear-propulsion-red-hot-radiators/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"He_162","CreatedById":152811,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T19:57:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222483219\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135386\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459367272\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152681\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gojira1000\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Gojira1000 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/94519-105-atomic-age-nuclear-propulsion-red-hot-radiators/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI addressed the fact that this is overpowered, and unlike any real life engine, it is not physically possible in the next 30 years to make such a small, and lightweight engine that runs on a nuclear reactor, and even so, the amount of lead needed to protect the people flying it would make it weigh much more than it does.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy mod is supposed to introduce the full reactor, and engine idea, one reactor, as many engines as the reactor will allow, this will be an endgame technology, and it will be useful for retrieving capsules that just got back to Kerbin from re-entry, or putting satellites into orbit cheaply, and safely. It can also be used to put spaceplanes into orbit without the need of a large fuel tank like the shuttle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry if I sound rude, but I addressed that this is a different kind of thing entirely, and I believe it would be just as popular as pork\u0027s mod for nuclear stuff. Perhaps I could contact him and have him incorporate the design into his mod?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gojira1000","CreatedById":152681,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T19:59:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust wasn\u0027t sure you knew PJAA existed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"He_162","CreatedById":152811,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T20:03:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222483256\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135386\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459367958\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152681\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gojira1000\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Gojira1000 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust wasn\u0027t sure you knew PJAA existed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh ok, yeah I knew. I checked out all the mods I could about nuclear engines before I posted this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}